				<td colspan="2"><span>I was in a group that was doing alright, but had the strange sort of people that never said anything except for a chanter and rogue. Well a CR augment dropped and 4 of us rolled and i won it. On the very next mob a Cha+ augment dropped. I asked the group if they cared if i rolled again since bards need cha and they all said no. 3 pass...chanter rolls a 75, and then the shammy out of nowhere rolls an 80. Now i'm thinking, WTF does a shammy need cha for, and don't say they have a charm animals spell cause i would be RL $ or plat that 99% have never casted it once in their life. What a jerk, cha is very useful to chanters and maybe useful for merchant fodder. I hate jerks like this. But in the end it didn't matter cause i rolled a 97. And asked the group once more if they cared if i took it. It would have sickened me to see a +cha aug go to a shammy. That'd be like seeing an FT4(oh wait it's mana regeneration now) item drop that was all/all and seeing a warrior take it.
<br />
/rant off</span></td>
