				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dropped LDoN augments<a name="28156"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 04 2:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
In a pick-up group, what stops someone from just lying?
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Nothing. 
<br />

<br />
Nothing makes me just assume a complete stranger is lying, either, though. I'm sure I've been lied to in the past and lost a chance on making some quick cash or getting an upgrade (not on augments, of course - just speaking of drops in general). I'm sure I'll be lied to in the future and lose out again on making some quick cash or getting an upgrade. I'd rather lose some fake money now and again or not get that extra +2AC that random_drop_001 would give me than automatically assume everyone (or even some small fraction thereof) I meet is going to lie to me, though.
<br />

<br />
I'm not at all opposed to non-NBG groups. I don't really care one way or another about it, as long as whichever rule is applied is applied consistently. 
<br />

<br />
My only complaint with NBG is that a lot of people don't realize that bards need INT and CHA. Well, that and priest classes who insist that they NEED that +5 dex augment just as much as the rogue or warrior does.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
