				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dropped LDoN augments<a name="28161"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 16 04 2:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes.  &quot;Need&quot; is super subjective isn't it?
<br />

<br />
Do bards &quot;need&quot; haste items?  I remember back when Cloak of Flames was the top haste item in the game, there were huge flamefests about whether bards should get to roll on a Cloak of Flames after a successful Naggy raid.  And forget bards a minute -- our group's shammy wants a haste cloak.  Does she &quot;need&quot; it?  Well, probably no.  Will she use it?  h*ll yes -- she likes to melee.  Are we going to get her one?  d*mn straight.  
<br />

<br />
And, just for the record although I'm not sure your post was meant to suggest to the contrary, I don't &quot;automatically assume everyone . . . I meet is going to lie to me.&quot;  As an example, we elected to believe our pick-up cleric and award him the MM boots.  My point is simply that NBG relies on trust and mutual honesty, and it's a lot easier to get that and to believe you're getting it with a regular group or guild group.  I'm sure there are lots of people on the Nameless who are perfectly honest, fair and forthright people yet also strangers to me.  I'm also 100% certain that there are a lot of pp grubbing loot ho's who are also strangers to me.  I see them in action every day.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
