				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dropped LDoN augments<a name="28926"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 19 04 12:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">With respect, can you prove that?
<br />

<br />
Lots of shammies believe to the contrary.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
The topic has been done to death on the Crucible, to the point that it's nothing more than a running joke anymore.  There is no evidence whatsoever to support the notion that 300 cha is any better than 40 cha for purposes of landing spells.  A quick search didn't turn up any parses, but I recall having seen one years ago that debunked it adequately for me.  The test subject was a troll shaman using a bunch of -CHA items then going for the highest CHA he could get up to.  Resist rates were within about 1-2%.  The post seems to be lost to antiquity though.  You could just ask on the Crucible if you'd like a second opinion, but I would highly recommend asbestos long johns and expect to see a bunch &quot;OMG SEARCH!!!!&quot; type posts if you do so. ;)
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=776546" target="_blank">Waeland Mistnote</a></br>
